<paragraph id="F32D5F2DFFECFFAFEDF2A2D8FD3CFBCC" blockId="18.[151,1436,506,1143]" pageId="18" pageNumber="491">
Notes. This species was described based on one male and one female specimen deposited in the USNM collection. A male cotype is here designated as 
<typeStatus id="2C29E18FFFECFFAFEF81A53DFCF5FB95" box="[692,795,1046,1071]" pageId="18" pageNumber="491">lectotype</typeStatus>
to fix the identity of the species. This species resembles 
<taxonomicName id="349224AEFFECFFAFEDA2A510FED8FBE9" authorityName="Melichar" authorityYear="1923" box="[151,310,1083,1107]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Makilingia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="491" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="intermedia">
<emphasis id="C1E6833FFFECFFAFEDA2A510FED8FBE9" box="[151,310,1083,1107]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="491">M. intermedia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but differs in having only a narrow yellow longitudinal stripe along the forewing commissure rather than a pair of large transcommissural yellow spots.
</paragraph>
